fields.value: Replication Data for: "Measuring Personal Beliefs and Perceived Norms about Intimate Partner Violence: Population-Based Survey Experiment in Rural Uganda"

dsDescriptionValue.value: This page contains the deidentified replication data for Tsai et al., "Measuring Personal Beliefs and Perceived Norms about Intimate Partner Violence: Population-Based Survey Experiment in Rural Uganda", PLOS Med, 2017. The dataset was created in Stata version 14.2. The do-file, when applied to the replication dataset, reproduces the analyses contained in the journal article. The log-file represents the output of the do-file when applied to the replication dataset.

publicationCitation.value: Tsai AC, Kakuhikire B, Perkins JM, Vořechovská D, McDonough AQ, Ogburn EL, et al. (2017) Measuring personal beliefs and perceived norms about intimate partner violence: Population-based survey experiment in rural Uganda. PLoS Med 14(5): e1002303. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pmed.1002303
